  "title": "Core Concepts of Introduction to Thai Cuisine in Practice",
  "lessonText": "Understanding the core concepts of Thai cuisine is essential for mastering its unique flavors.",
  "data": {
    "content": "Thai cuisine is characterized by its balance of flavors:\n- **Sweet**: Often derived from palm sugar or fruits.\n- **Sour**: Commonly from lime juice or tamarind.\n- **Salty**: Enhances the overall taste of dishes.\n- **Spicy**: Adds heat, typically from fresh chilies.\n- **Bitter**: Found in certain vegetables and herbs.\n\nTo cook Thai like a Thai, focus on quality ingredients. Each flavor plays a crucial role in creating the harmonious taste that Thai dishes are known for. Remember to practice filling in the blanks using the clues from the flashcards and concepts covered in this module to reinforce your understanding."
  }
